	<text>
		<body xml:lang="en">
			<div>

	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_002354_0001"/><!--pb/@n='82r'-->
<addSpan spanTo="#p82r-01" place="marginleft"><!--addSpan/@place='left hand margin of fol.82r'--></addSpan>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">next. I am &amp;c<reg>.</reg><persName>David Livingstone</persName></p><anchor xml:id="p82r-01"/>
<!--<p rend="center"><placeName>Limefield,</placeName> <lb/></p>
<p rend="center"><placeName>By West Calder.</placeName> <lb/></p>-->
<lb/><p rend="right">30<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> June 1865 </p>
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">My Dear <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Murray</persName></p>
<lb/><p><persName>Sir Roderick</persName>
<lb/>thinks that I had 
<lb/>better reply curtly 
<lb/>to a series of letters 
<lb/>translated from 
<lb/>the Lisbon official 
<lb/>journal &amp; published 
<lb/>by Stanford a 
<lb/>page would be 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_002354_0002"/><!--pb/@n='82v'-->
<lb/>enough or two pages 
<lb/>at most. The 
<lb/>pamphlet seizes 
<lb/>upon one foray 
<lb/>by a man called 
<lb/><persName>Belchior</persName> as the 
<lb/>whole matter 
<lb/>though for the 
<lb/>conduct of the 
<lb/>Governor of 
<lb/><placeName>Tette</placeName> I expressed 
<lb/>thanks. I have 
<lb/>put <persName>Rowley<reg>'</reg>s</persName>

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_002354_0003"/><!--pb/@n='83r'-->
<lb/>letter in a footnote 
<lb/>which disclaims 
<lb/>the inference they 
<lb/>have drawn &amp; 
<lb/>charges all <persName>bishop 
<lb/>Mackenzie<reg>'</reg>s</persName> disaster 
<lb/>on the Portuguese<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p>I had answered 
<lb/>the claim for 
<lb/>the discovery of 
<lb/><placeName>Lake Nyassa</placeName>
<lb/>in the appendix 
<lb/>but left it out<reg>.</reg>

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_002354_0004"/><!--pb/@n='83v'-->
<lb/>Do you think 
<lb/>it would be worth 
<lb/>while putting a 
<lb/>single leaf of an 
<lb/>appendix - in 
<lb/>in reply to this 
<lb/>thing. It proves 
<lb/>that the Portuguese 
<lb/>statesmen are 
<lb/>more implicated 
<lb/>than I imagined<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>The man is employed 
<lb/>by <persName>Colonel <unclear cert="low">Mumple 
<lb/>Leal.</unclear></persName> We go to <placeName>London</placeName>
<lb/>about Wednesday </p>

			
</div>
